The Continents of Aethelgard

    Zaloria

        The Shape: A sharp, majestic "Z".

        The Lore: The cradle of all life, the ancestral birthplace of the dragons, and where everything in the world originally came from.

    Grakos

        Dhurandal sword of Dhurandal

        Valinor. sword of Valinor



        The Shape: A heavy, sudden landmass.

        The Lore: A continent that recently drifted out of the unknown and crashed directly into Zaloria, shattering the coastline and creating a massive, scarred mountain range where they fused together.

    Dracomore

        The Shape: A perfect circle nestled inside a giant crescent moon 🌙.

        The Lore: The sacred dragon graveyard. It was originally just a normal landmass, but for millennia, dragons traditionally flew here to die. The continent is only alive and habitable today because of the magical, fertile soil created by the decaying dragon bones.

    Kragora

        The Shape: Jagged and fractured.

        The Lore: A lawless land of total anarchy. Brutal warlords constantly fight for control, carving out temporary territories that change every week, with no single ruler ever holding power for long.
